.SH NAME
dotty-profile-new - Create a system-level profile.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty profile new [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Create a profile directory under $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/dotty/\&. Without
--name dotty prompts for one. Unless --activate is given, dotty asks whether
to activate the new profile right away.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--activate\fP[=false]
	activate the profile after creating it

.PP
\fB--description\fP=""
	short description of the profile

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for new

.PP
\fB--name\fP=""
	name for the new profile


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty profile new
  dotty profile new --name=work --description="work laptop" --activate
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-profile(1)\fP
